  "subject": "KVM: Check for pending events before attempting injection",
  "body": "Instead of blindly attempting to inject an event before each guest entry,\ncheck for a possible event first in vcpu->requests.  Sites that can trigger\nevent injection are modified to set KVM_REQ_EVENT:\n\n- interrupt, nmi window opening\n- ppr updates\n- i8259 output changes\n- local apic irr changes\n- rflags updates\n- gif flag set\n- event set on exit\n\nThis improves non-injecting entry performance, and sets the stage for\nnon-atomic injection.\n\nSigned-off-by: Avi Kivity <avi@redhat.com>",
  "full_message": "KVM: Check for pending events before attempting injection\n\nInstead of blindly attempting to inject an event before each guest entry,\ncheck for a possible event first in vcpu->requests.  Sites that can trigger\nevent injection are modified to set KVM_REQ_EVENT:\n\n- interrupt, nmi window opening\n- ppr updates\n- i8259 output changes\n- local apic irr changes\n- rflags updates\n- gif flag set\n- event set on exit\n\nThis improves non-injecting entry performance, and sets the stage for\nnon-atomic injection.\n\nSigned-off-by: Avi Kivity <avi@redhat.com>",
